Sat Nov  8 19:20:03 UTC 2003  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0102

  1. PlanetMath mail will now by default result in an e-mail notification. 
     This can be turned off with a new preference, "Also send email for each 
     system notice?".

  2. The notification metadata for message posts/replies has been updated, so
     that the first few lines of the post content will actually appear as the
     comment of the notice. This also means users get a "preview" of the post
     within email, if they have notice emails turned on.  To accommodate this
     change, the subject of the post was combined with the subject of the 
     notice, as in 

       "Re: message post subject" (reply)

	 or 
  
       "message post subject" (post)

  3. Auto-hyperlinking of post content has been made much smarter.  It was 
     also failing regarding whitespace bugginess before.

  4. The post screen now has some guidance about entering posts as ASCII, and
     letting Noosphere do the hyperlinking automatically.

Wed Oct 15 04:40:44 UTC 2003  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0101

  1. Added parallel notice email feature.

Thu Jun 12 01:15:02 UTC 2003  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0100

  1. Added support for Mysql and switched PlanetMath over to Mysql.  There are
     plenty more bugs to stamp out here.

Wed Feb 26 06:18:32 UTC 2003  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0099

  1. Added multiple-editing colission handling: now check-outs are stamped with
     a version, and if the database version of an object goes up, the checked
     out version is not allowed in.  In this situation, the user is told to 
     go open a new edit for the object and to copy over/integrate the changes
     they were working on.

  2. Added a version roll-back for object owners.  This simply replaces the 
     current version of an object with the selected version (from the history
     page) and tosses out all revisions after it.   The rollback behavior could
     be nicer, but this should suffice for easy combatting of malicious edits.

