     "cancel" the correction without ever having to wait for the target user
     to reject it.  

  2. To go along with the above, the "edit corrections" functionality was split
     into two sections: "corrections to your objects", and "corrections you've
     filed".  From the latter, one can now click on "-" to retract a pending
     correction.

  3. When viewing a correction they have filed,  a "retract this correction"
     control appears.

Wed Sep 25 20:10:47 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0095

  1. Cleaned up login behavior.  No longer should double submits from clients
     cause people to get registered twice.  Also, the bug where being 
     registered twice prevented people from logging in has also been removed.

  2. Added account deactivation and reactivation.  When an account is 
     deactivated, the user cannot log in.  THey are informed of this when they
     attempt to log in.

  3. Added account deletion.  For content integrity purposes, this is not
     allowed unless the user hasn't created any objects.

  4. Added an admin control for the above to the user display page.

  5. Added globals to all templates, for things like site URLs.  This needs to
     be employed in all templates, so no locations are hardcoded.

