Sat Sep  7 22:32:50 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0091

  1. Removed "Typographical" correction type; added "Meta" correction type.
     Meta is typographical + anything about the entry's metadata (that is, not
     the mathematical content.)  Also made the correction filing screen more
     user-friendly, with an online help blurb for the types.

Wed Sep  4 12:58:38 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0090

  1. Added a "permissions" item to the user menu.  This is very similar to the
     ACL editor for a single object (in fact, the functionality was folded into
     the same subroutine), except it is of global scope.  Here, users can 
     configure their default ACL which gets applied to each new object they
     create, and they can retroactively apply this default ACL to all of their
     objects.

  2. Added a "view" item to the user box next to "your info" which lets users 
     quickly jump to their user info page, as others see it.

  3. Reworded some things on the "owner controls" box.

  4. Updated some statistics stuff; was missing deletion updates.

Sun Sep  1 10:07:29 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0089

  1. Added a "Statistics Caching" system (StatCache.pm) which eliminates the 
     need to frequently recalculate nontrivial statistics (for example, the top
     user list and latest additions/modifications are all extremely processor
     and disk intensive to produce).  Essentially, this "lazifies" the
     production of these statistics.  They are cached in a database hash and 
     can either be invalidated directly by portions of the system in response
     to events, or invalidated due to timeouts (this is useful for the 
     last-two-weeks top user list).  This should greatly increase the speed of
     the system.

Thu Aug 29 18:44:31 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0088

  1. Added "Typographical" correction type.

Tue Aug 27 21:40:31 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0087

  1. Moved "view history" control out of owner/admin boxes and into the display
     of each object's metadata that everyone can see.  There was really no 
     reason to hide this.

  2. Added convenient "create editor group" to the one-click control panel
     owners of an object see.  This allows the owner of an object to quickly
     create a group which has write permissions to that object.  After clicking
     this control, the user is placed in the group configuration screen.

  3. Greatly augmented the group "member editor" screen, such that it is now a
     generic "group configuration" screen.  Added title/description change 
     functionality and cleaned up the arrangement of widgets.

     Also, added auto name-to-id resolution, so users can input either name or
     user id to add members to their groups.  

     For when this fails, I've added a blurb explaining that you can simply 
     find users in the search engine, and directly add them to a group from 
     their "user info" page.

Tue Aug 27 00:45:45 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0086

  1. Rearranged and added to the "ACL editor" page.  Now there is a select box
     which allows the user to choose an existing group they admin to be the 
