Tue Aug 20 07:02:16 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0081

  1. Added a database admin interface.  It revolves around a freeform query
     interface, however, it is a little smarter: when possible, it slips oids
     into the result set of rows on a select, and uses these as keys to allow
     updates and deletes of arbitrary returned rows.  

     Also there is a "get info" command, and a table dropdown, so one can 
     quickly retrieve the schema and index information (as well as table size)
     for any table.

     Missing is a "query builder" interface, which would be especially useful
     for things like inserting new rows in arbitrary tables, based on their
     schema (perhaps this should be added by itself, since updates and deletes
     are fast enough using the freeform query interface.)

     Unfortunately, this is all very postgres-centric.  I don't see any way to
     generalize, not even through DBI.

Fri Aug  9 21:30:23 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0080

  1. Implemented "mathytitles."  This means that titles containing short math
     sequences like $\pi$ will be replaced with actual symbols.  This isn't
     exhaustive; its really only meant for representing very clumsy symbols
     or bb/cal fonts, or greek letters.  Things like $p$-adic will be left
     alone.  

  2. Cleaned up admin qwik-edit a bit and made it so that it actually saves
     version snapshots.

Fri Jul 26 16:19:51 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0079

  1. Put in the "prompt notice" system.  This allows notices to be sent which
     require (allow) a choice to be made, as a selection among alternatives. 
     When the user clicks on a choice (or deletes the notice), an action is
     performed.

  2. Used the above to add "Ask" as an option for accepting of symmetric
     "related" link behavior.  In other words, now you can set this preference 
     to "Ask" (instead of just "Yes" or "No"), and you will receive a prompt
     notice which allows one-click accepting (and zero-click rejecting) of 
     a related link which completes relation symmetry.

