Mon Jun 24 03:22:21 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0066

  1. Updated the encyclopedia alphabetical index.  Now goofy characters
     like quotes will not appear as index characters.  Also, names like
     "proof of X" are mangled to "X, proof of" for proper alphabetization.

     This was all achieved through expanding the objindex table and adding
     an index character (ichar field) which is derived from a mangled name
     at title indexing time.  Hence, the logic does not have to be repeated
     for each item at display time.
     
  2. Finally put in some date pretty-printing for messages.  Now you only
     see date and hour:minute.  The date is shown as month/day if the current
     year matches the message posting year, otherwise its yyyy-mm-dd.

