Wed May 22 08:54:40 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0056

  1. Added handling for international characters.  In specific, this means that
     linking works from TeX-forms of international strings to iso-8859-1
     internationalized strings.  

	 In addition, linking is done between properly internationalized titles
     in iso-8859-1 to raw ASCII strings which are "approximations" of the 
     internationalized versions.  So for example, "adele group" will link to
     an entry called "adèle group".

