Tue May  7 01:47:58 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0046

  1. Now SplitLaTeX() tries to escape bibliographies from automatic 
     linking.  This is done by escaping text beginning with one of the
     following strings, and continuing to the end of the entry:
      
      \begin{thebibliography}
      {\bf References}
      {\bf Further Reading}
    
	 Surely we will need to add more, in time.  Also, the recombining
     sub had to be updated to handle the fact that escaped portions can
     be nested; instead of simply looping through the escaped portions 
     once, it simply replaces all @@[0-9]+@@ found with the appropriate
     escaped sequence until there are no more of these escape codes left.

Mon May  6 07:31:36 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0045

  1. Small change in code, major ramifications: correction filers no longer
     get any points for accepted corrections to entries they have permissions
     to edit directly.  We don't prevent them from actually filing a
     correction, since this sort of bookkeeping can be useful.

     Changed code in closeCorrection().

