Tue Feb 26 12:09:07 UTC 2002  Aaron Krowne <akrowne@vt.edu> Note 0006

  1. Moved handling of \PMlinkescapeword and \PMlinkescapephrase to a new
     sub in Crossref.pm called getEscapedWords, which is called in makelinks().
     This shifts the implementation of these pseudo-commands from an a-priori
     substring removal of the desired string from the latex to an a-posteriori
     check on the titles on which links were produced for the entry.  The old
     behavior would also kill linking of "mean value theorem" if the user 
     requested \PMlinkescapeword{mean} (bug 12).  This is no longer a problem.

